org.intermine.bio.dataconversion

Class IdResolverService

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.intermine.bio.dataconversion.IdResolverService

  • public final class IdResolverService
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper class to provide IdResolver service. Notes: 1. user can configure which resolver they want to use in a properties file? e.g. NCBI and flybase both can resolver fly genes, set priority? 2. resolver reads specific data format, the code is depended on data file. It need to reach to a consensus with MODs. In IdResolverFactory, the method createFromFile will do the parsing. One way to generalise the process is to configure in a properties file to let the class know the identifier information by column. e.g. type=tab, column.0=mainId, etc. 3. any instance of resolver should be caching during build 4. data sync issue: NCBI entrez info might be out of sync with other MOD datasets 5. how to add new resolver? By reflection? Notes: Unit tests: as all methods in this class are wrappers, it isn't worth writing tests if those wrapped methods are tested.
